tip.text: Really good pasta and lasagna and generally good Italian food. Family run restaurant.
Amazing pasta and Underrated Italian place. The food is lovely and amazing. It's a homely vibe here. Like a family serving you with authentic homemade Italian style dishes. This is one not to miss.
Lovely latte and food selection.
Not the best but it's okay. Pastries were too sweet for my liking. Found a hair in my choc dessert and the gelatine used for one of their dessert was excessive it tastes like soft rubber.
Ordered the coq au vin.Not bad in taste but I personally find it to just b Mediocre frenchfood.I've tasted more flavourful ones so if ur not d type that likes food too rich,this place would be ideal.
I guess it's just okay. I reckon u can get better Ones or pastries at par  somewhere else for a better price. If ur here for the brand do go ahead :)
Beautiful museum. Lots of tourist taking photos but well, it's a must do in Paris. Don't skip this area. It really is beautiful!
Such a beautiful site to see. Although there are loads of people but I reckon it's worth the trip here. It really is pretty when ur standing right before it.
It's a beautiful church. There is a small park nearby Over looking Paris which has a Beautiful view. However lots of people during summer time. As usual. Ahah. And few hills to climb up too.

location.address: 35 rue du Chevalier de la Barre
formattedAddress: 35 rue du Chevalier de la Barre

tip.text: Quaint little place tucked away from the hustling and bustling of Paris. Reasonable tasting menu served. Friendly staff and service. Very interesting food. Worth the visit.
Beautiful garden behind. Perfect for summer and order ur pizza from Santa Maria. Best pizza in Ealing.
Lovely selection. Get their homemade cakes. Lovely and taste delicious. High end grocery shop so be ready to spend but guaranteed top quality.
Mediocre scones. A bit slow with service. I'd rather pay a small and quaint decent cafe for their scones(which I'm sure taste better too)  and service than to dine here.
Great for a quick bite. Decent food and beverages at a reasonable price. Great cake selection.
Very good coffee and desserts served here. Great for a quick stop for a cuppa and take out to go.
Always just go for the crème brûlée or salted banana doughnut. Matcha was a bit of a disappointment. Stick to the doughy donuts and don't bother ordering cake donut.
Good lunch offer, friendly service. Beef burger was juicy and really flavourful. The coleslaw however was a disappointment. Opt for the fries. Safest bet.
Dry aged grilled beef burger smothered with mac and cheese. That's the thing you should get. Creative cocktails served here too. Great for group gathering.
Mung bean pancakes, fish cake, Korean rice cake, kim bap

Lots of Traditional and authentic. Most of stalls serve pretty good korean food. Get the kim bap(rice rolls with pickled vege) and the sweet potato noodles and spicy Korean rice cake.Great for foodies
You can't go wrong with the desserts and baked good here. A bit pricey but worth the trip and calories. Get the strawberry short cake and éclairs!!
Amazing calamari! This was the highlight here. Pizza was just okay. If go for the starters and drinks here. ! Definitely order the calamari though.
Their fish and chips is amazing ! Try their haggis too. It doesn't taste as bad. Warning don't read what haggis is before trying it. Gets really crowded as it's situated in a tourist spot !
Restaurant with a Scenic view overlooking London city. Don't order their signature dish and go straight fr other mains. Their Pasta is delicious but the star was really their rosemary garlic bread.
My favorite bakery in London. Highly recommended for fresh sourdough bread , almond croissant is to die for. Service and coffee wasn't really good  but glad the food made up for that.
Chocolate heaven for chocolate lovers.
If you like an interesting take on middle eastern food and specialty cocktail/mocktails head here. Friendly service. Gets really crowded so reservations recommended.
You will not regret heading here. Lisbon has amazing food and what more under one roof. Highly recommend to visit this big food market. Authentic and traditional delicacies served here.
You have to visit this chain bakery. They serve all their authentic baked goods. One of my favorite is their coconut buns called pão de deus (pao means bread) and an almond custard cake.
Try their XL scones. A bit skimpy on the jam and butter. But a nice tea break after a good hike from the caste and palace.
Authentic meals served here. Amazing shellfish stew. The food here if fresh and has a very homey taste. And less touristy too! Highly recommended.
Very fresh seafood. Highly recommended if you'd like simple and really fresh seafood. Gets really crowded. Best to go when they just open at 12pm !
Wtf ?! Cooked sushi tuna ? Better call it mayo cucumber. So not worth it. I'm so disappointed.

location.address: SK3 Promenade 2/F, 1 Utama Shopping Centre, 1 Lebuh Bandar Utama, Bandar Utama City Centre

tip.text: Their lunch meals are so worth it. Love the interior as well. Friendly service team. I would definitely come back. Thi parking may be a tad problem here.
Coffee is pretty good. Pair them with some of the sweet stuff in the market. Goes really well. Friendly service !
Absolutely amazing Nordic food served here. Love their butter and bread and their dishes are spectacular. Would definitely recommend.
In love with Nordic designs and good place to buy gifts home. Very pretty things.
Quick and fast Taiwanese food. Dumplings were yummy. Their noodles was peanut sauce was a bit odd for me in terms of flavour. But worth a try. Efficient and fast service too.
The sausage was just mediocre. However the fries were fried to perfection.
First stop in Berlin. German cheesecake was not too sweet. Different texture than ur regular cheesecake. Lighter and not so dense. Wasn't too bad. Would recommend if u like lighter cheesecake.
Please get the honey cake. You won't regret it.
Nasi kerabu. Nasi kerabu.

tip.text: Amazing view. Very nice suites available for a reasonable price. However the pool is a little disappointing. Too many people taking photos.Convenient location tho public transport may be a little hard
I would highly recommend their rice bowls. Tucked away from the hustling city. Located in a quaint neighbourhood. Gets pack during lunch and seats may be limited indoors.

venue.name: Sin Lee Foods 新利合記

tip.text: Their kaya toast is to die for. Also try their rice bowl. High recommended. Tho parking may be a little tricky here but definitely worth it :)
Live their pizza here. Very authentic Italian food situated in a quiet neighbourhood.
Good selection of Australian meals. Situated in very quiet neighbourhood. A hidden gem.

tip.text: It was beautiful and definitely worth to hike at. Breath taking beautify of Mother Nature. Some parts gets a bit too steep so be careful with your leg and steps.
Love their French toast and salmon dish. Gets a tad bit busy during brunch. Communal table was a bit uncomfortable tho. But overall was a good brunch place.
Oh their fried rice is yummy and other food too. So affordable for the portion. Good service and comfortable setting too. Real cheap and good Thai food. Highly recommended
Authentic Indian food in a home. Spicy and tasty. They put a little saffron in their water so don't be fooled if u think it's dirty.
Gelato! Best in Melbourne. Generous scoop and so damn amazing. For a raspberry swirl and love the chunks of fruits in my gelato.
Their buttermilk chicken burger is worth trying. However too much mushrooms on the potato has in my opinion. Great for sharing tho.
Maple walnut hands down the best. 😋
Love the hot cakes. And their mork hot chocolate is amazing too. Especially on a cold day 😃

tip.text: Good place for a donut stop.
Their spicy seafood tofu soup and fried chicken is a must. Add cheese. It's goooooooood. Gets busy during peak hours tho.
Good breakfast spread. Service was wonderful. Staff was very helpful. Love the gym facility. However the beach ain't got nothing impressive. If you want a relaxing holiday then this would be ideal.

contact.facebookName: The Westin Langkawi Resort and Spa

tip.text: Wish they used better quality ice cream. Nonetheless good molten chocolate cake :) feels a little dodgy at night if you sit outdoors. Recommend sitting inside if ur alone or with ur girlfriends.

Their waffle is amazing.Crispy outside,fluffy in the inside.Best I have tasted so far in Pj I reckon.They have various toppings n they make their own ice cream too! Get your waffle cravings fixed here
The interior is amazing. So cosy. Coffee is not too bad. A little too sweet for my liking. Nonetheless. Worth the visit of u want to chill and relax :) food looks interesting too!

tip.text: Banana butterscotch 😍😍😍. Love how well they fold their Danish pastries. Good pastries I reckon. Small but Cosy place to have some pastries with drinks. Friendly service too :)
Nice and Cosy place to chill. Their coffee is too strong for my liking. If u love strong n rich coffee then u might enjoy it better.

tip.text: Their salted egg sotong and Chinese fried crullers are my ultimate favourite !
Hike, scenery. Nature walk

tip.text: Their French toast is good. Haven't been back here since a year and a half ago.the service and quality of food has improved tremendously. Keep up the good work and don't fall back!
French toast. By far the best I have tasted in Kuala Lumpur. Love the ambiance too especially when it's raining :)
Green curry&fried fish was excellent.Below is porkbelly&softshellcrab.Try their fusion dishes with brown rice as it pairs perfectly.Service was efficient and welcoming.definitely coming back again.
If you're looking for a rich hot chocolate. This is the place. Very friendly service. Scones&Pancake itself were good, however I wish they'd use better sausage and ingredients for the steep price.

tip.text: Simple, homey local cooking with a twist. Menu is well executed I reckon.
The coffee and hot chocolate is as good as you can get in ones in Melbourne.love how their toilet is so clean. Really love the vibe and interior. They put a lt of thought into everything inside.
The croissants. Especially the molten salted egg one. 😍👍. Incredible service and such a cosy place to have tea and just simple enjoy some freshly made pastries,bread and coffee.
Must mUST MUST have the hot cakes. And the steak sandwich. Contented with the both of that. Very pack so be patient and wait cuz it's so worth it.
Just get the beef pho. The broth was so flavorful. Quite a big portion for AUD10. Highly recommended if ur looking for some pho on a cold winter day/night.
Piña colada cruffin is amazing.great combination of flavors.wanted to try other cruffin flavors but I came late around 3 smth.Most of the stuff r already sold out.friendly service.Highly recommended
Kayaking. If ur in Malaysia and ur up for an outdoor adventure away from the city. This is the place to go.
Their berry pavlova is excellent. Ceviches are good. Soft shell crab nachos. Good for dates and stunning view of klcc just right across fuego.

Grilled chicken salad👍👍👍 very cost environment.
They came up with this burger. So good. This place has been my fav jap childhood restaurant. Taste is still there even after 10 years. Service could be better. But well I love the food so no fuss.
So beautiful

tip.text: Beautiful beach. They have a few massage parlor and water sports by the beach. Service is excellent. Room service food is extremely good however I wish they'd do something about their b/fast spread.
Still by far the best ramly in town.
Celebrated a beautiful wedding in such a beautiful church.
Greeted warmly by the service crew. :) great place to chill. However a little disappointed with the dessert here. Doesn't really taste like apple crumble IMO. Need More room for improvement on that:)
Pandan chicken and otak otak. I don't usually eat otak2 but the one here is delicious. Lotsa varieties on the menu didn't get the chance to try most of it. Very cooling, good service and good food.
Everything on the menu :) beautiful art on the wall and love their quote :)
